      "Bash(git commit -m \"$\\(cat <<''EOF''\nadd trivia settings store with localStorage persistence\n\n- Settings store with configurable rounds, questions per round, timer duration\n- localStorage sync for persisting game preferences\n- Tests for all store actions and localStorage integration\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "Bash(git commit -m \"$\\(cat <<''EOF''\nfeat: complete optimization tasks T1-T9\n\nThis commit includes all 9 optimization tasks:\n\n- fix\\(bingo\\): T1 - fix audio memory leak in audio-store\n  - Added cleanup function to release audio resources after playback\n  - Audio src and event handlers cleared after use\n\n- fix\\(bingo\\): T2 - fix auto-call race condition in use-game hook\n  - Added isProcessingRef to prevent concurrent calls\n  - Proper timeout cleanup on pause/unmount\n\n- feat\\(config\\): T3 - add ENV variable validation for supabase clients\n  - Both apps now fail fast with clear errors for missing ENV vars\n\n- refactor\\(sync\\): T4 - consolidate BroadcastSync to shared package\n  - Deleted duplicate broadcast.ts from both apps\n  - All imports now use @beak-gaming/sync\n\n- refactor\\(sync\\): T5 - consolidate session utilities to shared package\n  - Deleted duplicate session utilities from trivia app\n\n- refactor\\(bingo\\): T6 - use shared Slider from @beak/ui\n  - Deleted local Slider.tsx, using @beak-gaming/ui\n\n- feat\\(ui\\): T7 - add error boundaries to both apps\n  - Senior-friendly error UI with large refresh button\n  - Errors logged to console for debugging\n\n- feat\\(a11y\\): T8 - add ARIA labels to presenter components\n  - Added roles and aria-labels to BingoBoard, ControlPanel\n  - Added accessibility attributes to QuestionDisplay, TeamManager\n\n- test\\(bingo\\): T9 - add tests for audio and auto-call fixes\n  - Memory leak prevention tests for audio-store\n  - Race condition prevention tests for use-game\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "Bash(git commit -m \"$\\(cat <<''EOF''\nfix\\(e2e\\): complete auth rate limit false positive fix \\(BEA-358\\)\n\nAdd URL verification to catch blocks in auth fixture to prevent false\npositive rate limit detection. After successful navigation away from\nthe login page, game error pages may contain \"try again\" text that\nmatches rate limit patterns.\n\nChanges:\n- loginViaPlatformHub: Add page.url\\(\\).includes\\(''/login''\\) check at line 175\n- authenticatedPage fixture: Add page.url\\(\\).includes\\(''/login''\\) check at line 324\n\nThis complements the previous fix that added URL checks at lines 146 and 299\nin the rateLimitCheckPromise, completing coverage of all rate limit detection\npaths.\n\nTest results: 92 failures -> 81 failures \\(11 fewer false positives\\)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
      "Bash(git commit -m \"$\\(cat <<''EOF''\nfix\\(e2e\\): remove redundant modal waits in Bingo tests \\(BEA-361\\)\n\nRemove redundant waitForRoomSetupModal\\(\\) calls from dual-screen tests.\nThe authenticatedBingoPage fixture already dismisses the modal, so these\ncalls were causing 10-second timeouts waiting for a modal that would never\nappear.\n\nChanges:\n- Remove waitForRoomSetupModal from 3 dual-screen tests:\n  - multiple balls sync correctly\n  - pattern change syncs to display\n  - closing display does not affect presenter\n- Add test.use\\({ skipModalDismissal: true }\\) to modal-timing.spec.ts\n  so those tests can actually test the modal behavior\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
